690
00:56:32.553 --> 00:56:35.681
But this is an emergency !
Dad's in love.

691
00:56:35.848 --> 00:56:38.142
Get out of here !
Dad doesn't fall in love.

692
00:56:38.308 --> 00:56:40.185
I mean,
at least not seriously.

693
00:56:40.352 --> 00:56:42.604
Trust me.
He's serious about this one.

694
00:56:42.771 --> 00:56:45.315
He's always holding her hand
and kissing her neck...

695
00:56:45.482 --> 00:56:47.317
and waiting on her
hand and foot.

696
00:56:47.484 --> 00:56:49.820
- He is?
- It's disgusting.

697
00:56:49.987 --> 00:56:52.865
Well, you'll just have to break 'em up.
Sabotage her. Do whatever you have to.

698
00:56:53.031 --> 00:56:55.868
I'm trying, but, I mean,
I'm at a slight disadvantage.

699
00:56:56.034 --> 00:56:58.787
I only met the man
12 hours ago.

700
00:56:58.954 --> 00:57:01.248
Hal, you've got to get
back here to help me.

701
00:57:01.415 --> 00:57:04.334
Annie, I can't.
I want more time with Mom.

702
00:57:04.501 --> 00:57:06.670
What's going on?

703
00:57:06.837 --> 00:57:09.047
Ann, are you still there?
I can barely hear you. Ann.

704
00:57:09.214 --> 00:57:11.800
- I'm here. What do you--
- Operator. Operator.

705
00:57:11.967 --> 00:57:14.344
- I think I lost you, Ann.
- Hello?

706
00:57:14.511 --> 00:57:18.140
Thanks for all the help, Hal.

707
00:57:21.226 --> 00:57:25.022
Hi. I had a phone call
from a friend at camp.

708
00:57:25.188 --> 00:57:27.274
Yeah. I-It's
an old camp tradition.

709
00:57:27.441 --> 00:57:31.528
Talk to your friend from
inside a closet. [ Laughs ]
Kinda stupid, I know, but--

710
00:57:31.695 --> 00:57:37.451
So, breakfast anyone?

711
00:57:37.618 --> 00:57:41.663
Okay. Here we go.
Most important meal of the day.

712
00:57:41.830 --> 00:57:44.917
Eggs sunny-side up,
bacon, side of toast...

713
00:57:45.083 --> 00:57:46.919
and, in case you're
really hungry,

714
00:57:47.085 --> 00:57:49.755
a stack of humongous chocolate chip
pancakes, which smell incredible,

715
00:57:49.922 --> 00:57:54.051
- if I do say so myself.
- Thanks, Chessy.

716
00:57:54.217 --> 00:57:56.386
You're not hungry again?

717
00:57:56.553 --> 00:57:58.305
You hardly touched your chili,
your favourite food in the world.

718
00:57:58.472 --> 00:58:00.807
And now you don't want breakfast?
Are you sick, honey?

719
00:58:00.974 --> 00:58:02.893
I'm fine.
I promise.

720
00:58:03.060 --> 00:58:04.895
Where's Dad?

721
00:58:05.062 --> 00:58:07.564
Oh. He and Miss "I'll Just Have
Half A Grapefruit, Thank You"...

722
00:58:07.731 --> 00:58:09.650
left about
an hour ago.

723
00:58:09.816 --> 00:58:12.277
You overslept,
and he didn't want to wake you.

724
00:58:12.444 --> 00:58:14.613
Of course, I'd probably oversleep, too,
if I were up until midnight...

725
00:58:14.780 --> 00:58:16.990
making mysterious phone calls
from my bathroom.

726
00:58:17.157 --> 00:58:20.035
Oh. Oh. That.

727
00:58:20.202 --> 00:58:22.120
I was calling a friend
from camp, Mildred.

728
00:58:22.287 --> 00:58:24.831
She lives
in New York.

729
00:58:24.998 --> 00:58:27.876
Oh, I see. So, you wanted
to wait and call Mildred...

730
00:58:28.043 --> 00:58:31.088
at a time that was convenient for her
because of the time difference.

731
00:58:31.254 --> 00:58:33.674
Exactly. Because--
Because of the time difference.

732
00:58:33.840 --> 00:58:37.344
Uh-huh. So, you waited until it was
3:00 in the morning her time?

733
00:58:37.511 --> 00:58:40.639
- That makes perfect sense.
- Actually--

734
00:58:41.932 --> 00:58:43.767
It was 7:00 at night
her time.

735
00:58:43.934 --> 00:58:45.769
You see, she lives in New York,
but she was on vacation...

736
00:58:45.936 --> 00:58:47.771
with her family
in Bora Bora.

737
00:58:50.148 --> 00:58:54.653
Very smooth.

738
00:58:54.820 --> 00:58:57.322
Okay, look, smarty pants,
your father wants you...

739
00:58:57.489 --> 00:58:59.491
to meet him at his office as soon
as you're done with breakfast.

740
00:58:59.658 --> 00:59:02.160
He does?
Thanks.

741
00:59:02.327 --> 00:59:04.329
I'm done.

742
00:59:08.667 --> 00:59:10.502
That dog
has gotten so weird.

743
00:59:10.669 --> 00:59:13.338
Bye, Chessy. Thanks again
for breakfast. It was great.

744
00:59:16.049 --> 00:59:18.969
Push, Hal.

745
00:59:19.136 --> 00:59:22.848
Sorry. I... forgot.

746
00:59:28.478 --> 00:59:31.022
Honey, I'm really glad
you're here,

747
00:59:31.189 --> 00:59:34.025
'cause there's something really
important I want to talk to you about.

748
00:59:34.192 --> 00:59:38.196
That's funny, because there's
something really important that
I want to talk to you about.

749
00:59:38.363 --> 00:59:40.782
- Yeah? Well, you go first.
- No, you.

750
00:59:40.949 --> 00:59:45.370
Okay. I want to talk to you
about Meredith.

751
00:59:45.537 --> 00:59:48.748
And I want to talk to you
about my mother.

752
00:59:48.915 --> 00:59:52.627
- What about Meredith?
- Well, what about your mother?

753
00:59:52.794 --> 00:59:54.838
Dad, I'm almost 12.
How long do you expect me...

754
00:59:55.005 --> 00:59:57.883
to buy that story that the stork
dropped me on your doorstep?

755
00:59:58.049 --> 01:00:01.219
Oh, come on, Hal.
We've talked about your mother.

756
01:00:01.386 --> 01:00:03.430
No, we haven't.
Not really.

757
01:00:03.597 --> 01:00:06.975
A girl needs more in life than
a half a crumpled old photograph.

758
01:00:07.142 --> 01:00:08.977
Dad, I'm almost
a teenager.

759
01:00:09.144 --> 01:00:11.062
Face it.
I need a mother.

760
01:00:11.229 --> 01:00:13.356
You know what?
You're right.

761
01:00:13.523 --> 01:00:17.903
You're absolutely right. You do need
a mother. Which brings me to--

762
01:00:20.614 --> 01:00:23.283
- Meredith.
- Hi. Hello, Hal.

763
01:00:23.408 --> 01:00:25.243
Hi.

764
01:00:25.410 --> 01:00:27.412
Hallie, this is
my assistant, Richard.

765
01:00:27.579 --> 01:00:30.290
Richard, this is Nick's daughter, the
one I've been telling you so much about.

766
01:00:30.457 --> 01:00:33.251
- Oh, hello. How are you?
- Hi there.

767
01:00:33.418 --> 01:00:35.754
- Did you tell her?
- Almost.

768
01:00:35.921 --> 01:00:37.923
- [ Sighs ]
- Hey, if you're free later,

769
01:00:38.089 --> 01:00:39.925
why don't we all
have lunch on the terrace?

770
01:00:40.091 --> 01:00:43.595
Well, actually, I promised Hal
we'd hang out together this afternoon.

771
01:00:43.762 --> 01:00:46.306
Oh, no problem.
I've got plenty to do.

772
01:00:46.473 --> 01:00:50.268
I'm working on a new label design,
Nicky, featuring Y-O-U.

773
01:00:50.435 --> 01:00:53.104
You're gonna love it.
See you for dinner, darling.

774
01:00:53.271 --> 01:00:56.608
- Bye, Hal.
- Bye.

775
01:00:56.775 --> 01:00:58.985
The first change I make is to send
that two-faced little brat...

776
01:00:59.152 --> 01:01:01.237
off to boarding-school
in Timbuktu.

777
01:01:01.404 --> 01:01:03.281
Ooh. Ice Woman !

778
01:01:03.448 --> 01:01:05.533
And proud of it, babe.

779
01:01:12.582 --> 01:01:15.418
Come on, Dad.

780
01:01:19.673 --> 01:01:21.591
Okay. Okay. You win.

781
01:01:21.758 --> 01:01:24.260
Pull up.
Give that horse a rest.

782
01:01:24.427 --> 01:01:26.763
Whoa, Sprout.

783
01:01:26.930 --> 01:01:30.558
So, honey, are you excited
about our camping trip?

784
01:01:30.725 --> 01:01:33.500
- What camping trip?
- What camping trip?

785
01:01:33.512 --> 01:01:37.000
The one we take every summer
before you go back to school.


787
01:01:37.190 --> 01:01:41.528
Oh. Oh. That camping trip.
Yeah. Sure. I can't wait.

788
01:01:41.695 --> 01:01:44.999
So, uh, Hal.

789
01:01:46.500 --> 01:01:47.283
What do you think of Meredith?

790
01:01:47.450 --> 01:01:49.000
As what, Dad?

791
01:01:49.001 --> 01:01:52.707
Your... Your publicist, 
your friend, your...

792
01:01:52.708 --> 01:01:57.168
No. Just what do you think
of her as a person?

793
01:01:57.335 --> 01:01:59.129
Oh. She's cute.

794
01:01:59.130 --> 01:02:01.131
She has nice hair, good teeth.

795
01:02:01.297 --> 01:02:03.174
She can spell the word "you."

796
01:02:03.341 --> 01:02:06.344
Honestly, Dad, the woman is
a complete stranger to me.

797
01:02:06.511 --> 01:02:08.471
Why do you
want my opinion, anyway?

798
01:02:08.638 --> 01:02:10.515
Well, I'll tell you why, Hal.

799
01:02:10.682 --> 01:02:13.685
- Because, believe it or not--
- Race you back to the ranch, Dad.

800
01:02:13.852 --> 01:02:16.271
H-Hal.

801
01:02:16.438 --> 01:02:20.275
Hal, I'm trying
to tell you something.

802
01:02:22.694 --> 01:02:25.196
Hey !
Slow down.

1
01:02:47,000 --> 01:02:51,340
I'm in so over my head here.
I can't handle this, I just can't.

876
01:02:51,350 --> 01:02:53,770
I'm only one kid. <i>(gasps) </i>

877
01:02:53,790 --> 01:02:55,710
You got something you want to 
share with the class  there, Hal? 

878
01:02:55,720 --> 01:02:58,280
Chessy, you gave me a fright.

879
01:03:00,000 --> 01:03:02,159
I gave you a fright? 

880
01:03:02,160 --> 01:03:06,920
You scared me. 
I didn't know you were, like, in here.

881
01:03:06,930 --> 01:03:11,890
Are you sure there isn't anything 
 you want to talk to me about? 

882
01:03:11,900 --> 01:03:15,760
Like why Sammy 
 never comes near you anymore.

883
01:03:15,770 --> 01:03:20,230
or why your appetite's 
 changed.

884
01:03:20,250 --> 01:03:23,170
Or why all of a sudden you're 
 neat as a pin

885
01:03:23,180 --> 01:03:27,710
and using expressions like, 
 "You gave me a fright."

886
01:03:27,720 --> 01:03:32,340
Chessy, I changed a lot 
 over the summer, that's all.

887
01:03:32,760 --> 01:03:33,310
OK.

888
01:03:35,090 --> 01:03:40,280
Boy, if I didn't know 
 any better, I'd say 
 it's almost like you were...

889
01:03:40,870 --> 01:03:43,020
Forget it. It's impossible.

890
01:03:43,030 --> 01:03:45,860
Almost as if I were who, 
 Chessy? 

891
01:03:45,870 --> 01:03:48,430
Nobody. Nobody. Forget 
 I mentioned it.

892
01:03:48,440 --> 01:03:51,070
Almost as if I were... Annie? 

893
01:04:00,990 --> 01:04:03,800
You know about Annie?

894
01:04:03,850 --> 01:04:05,340
I am Annie.

895
01:04:06,360 --> 01:04:07,850
<i>(Nick) </i> Hal.

896
01:04:09,230 --> 01:04:12,120
Hal, why did you take off 
 on me like that? 

897
01:04:12,300 --> 01:04:15,350
I told you I wanted to 
 talk to you about something.

898
01:04:16,370 --> 01:04:20,320
Chessy, why are you looking at her like that? 

899
01:04:20,870 --> 01:04:24,100
Like what? I'm not looking 
 at her any special way.

900
01:04:24,110 --> 01:04:27,430
I'm looking at her like I've 
 looked at her for 11 years.

901
01:04:27,450 --> 01:04:31,070
Since the day she came home 
 from the hospital.

902
01:04:31,080 --> 01:04:35,510
Six pounds, 11 ounces. 21 inches long. 
 This is how I look at her.

903
01:04:36,250 --> 01:04:38,810
Can I hug her? 

904
01:04:40,820 --> 01:04:44,410
Oh, she's so beautiful.

905
01:04:44,830 --> 01:04:47,020
And so big.

906
01:04:47,570 --> 01:04:51,290
I'm going to make you 
 something special to eat. 
 What would you like? Anything? 

907
01:04:51,300 --> 01:04:52,830
You know what, 
 it doesn't matter.

908
01:04:52,840 --> 01:04:56,260
I'm just gonna go whip up 
 everything we've got. OK? 

909
01:04:56,270 --> 01:04:58,570
Hal, come here.

910
01:04:59,580 --> 01:05:02,270
- We have to talk. 

911
01:05:02,280 --> 01:05:03,260
OK. Shoot.

912
01:05:03,350 --> 01:05:05,210
OK.

913
01:05:05,220 --> 01:05:08,080
Honey...

914
01:05:08,090 --> 01:05:13,110
I want to know what you think 
 about making Meredith 
 part of the family.

915
01:05:13,390 --> 01:05:17,890
Part of our family? - Yeah.

916
01:05:17,900 --> 01:05:20,390
- I think 
 it's an awesome idea. 
 - Yeah? 

917
01:05:20,400 --> 01:05:23,960
- Inspired! Brilliant! 
 - You do? Really? You do? 

918
01:05:23,970 --> 01:05:28,020
Totally. I mean, like it's 
 a dream come true. I've always 
 wanted a big sister.

919
01:05:28,210 --> 01:05:31,900
Oh.

920
01:05:31,910 --> 01:05:34,300
Um... Honey, I think you're 
 kind of missing the point.

921
01:05:34,310 --> 01:05:38,010
No, I'm not. You're going 
 to adopt Meredith.

922
01:05:38,020 --> 01:05:42,710
- That is so sweet, Dad. 
 - No, I am not going to adopt her.

923
01:05:42,990 --> 01:05:47,120
I'm... going to marry her.

924
01:05:47,260 --> 01:05:49,310
Marry her? That's insane.

925
01:05:49,590 --> 01:05:52,490
How can you marry 
 a woman young enough 
 to be my big sister? 

926
01:05:52,500 --> 01:05:55,290
<i>Mais tu plaisantes, j'espère. 
 Meredith, ce n'est pas 
 une fille pour toi.</i>

927
01:05:55,300 --> 01:05:57,160
<i>Mais c'est pas possible, 
 je rêve. Qu'est-ce qui...</i>

928
01:05:57,170 --> 01:06:00,390
Calm down. Hal!

929
01:06:00,410 --> 01:06:03,200
Are you speaking French? 

930
01:06:03,210 --> 01:06:06,170
I learned it at camp.

931
01:06:06,180 --> 01:06:08,540
OK. I'm sorry.

932
01:06:08,550 --> 01:06:12,470
Let's discuss this calmly. 
 Calmly and rationally.

933
01:06:12,480 --> 01:06:15,040
Yeah, and in English, 
 if you don't mind. Right? 

934
01:06:15,050 --> 01:06:17,140
OK.

935
01:06:17,160 --> 01:06:19,610
Sweetheart, 
 what has gotten into you? 

936
01:06:19,620 --> 01:06:23,250
Nothing. Nothing. Just...

937
01:06:23,260 --> 01:06:27,450
Dad, you can't get married. 
 It'll totally ruin 
 completely everything.

938
01:06:27,500 --> 01:06:30,360
Hal. Hal.

939
01:06:30,370 --> 01:06:32,530
Hallie.

940
01:06:32,540 --> 01:06:35,160
Don't look at me. 
 I don't know a thing.

941
01:06:36,340 --> 01:06:38,900
<i>(music blasts from car stereo) </i>

942
01:06:51,020 --> 01:06:56,050
She thought I was going to adopt her? 

943
01:06:56,230 --> 01:06:58,120
Hi, doll. - Hi.

944
01:06:59,160 --> 01:07:04,090
Oh. You look stressed, baby.

945
01:07:04,230 --> 01:07:07,460
How about a martini? - How about a double? 

946
01:07:07,970 --> 01:07:09,930
Coming right up.

947
01:07:09,940 --> 01:07:12,700
Chessy!

948
01:07:14,010 --> 01:07:18,340
Don't you love it? 
 It's just what we need, 
 it's such a big house. Chessy!

949
01:07:22,500 --> 01:07:23,900
You rang? 

950
01:07:24,000 --> 01:07:25,350
Two martinis, please.

951
01:07:25,660 --> 01:07:28,080
And make Mr. Parker's 
 a double.

952
01:07:29,590 --> 01:07:33,750
Chess, please. 
 I'm getting a migraine.

953
01:07:37,270 --> 01:07:40,360
- I told Hallie. 
 - You did? And? 

954
01:07:40,370 --> 01:07:42,260
She went ballistic.

955
01:07:42,270 --> 01:07:45,970
She started yelling in French. 
 I didn't even know 
 she spoke French.

956
01:07:45,980 --> 01:07:48,500
- I don't know what's gotten into her. 
 - Oh, Nicky.

957
01:07:48,510 --> 01:07:51,170
This reaction 
 is totally classic.

958
01:07:51,180 --> 01:07:54,310
It's "Daddy's 
 Getting Remarried 101."

959
01:07:54,320 --> 01:07:57,180
I'd be worried 
 if she didn't act this way.

960
01:07:57,190 --> 01:07:59,010
Look.

961
01:07:59,020 --> 01:08:02,420
Why don't I go talk to her? 
 You know, woman-to-woman.

962
01:08:02,430 --> 01:08:07,150
I think she's a little 
 sensitive about you right now.

963
01:08:07,170 --> 01:08:12,430
That's why I need to do it. 
 We've got to 
 break the ice sometime.

964
01:08:12,440 --> 01:08:17,930
Wear your shirt like this. 
 I like it when 
 I can see a little chest hair.

965
01:08:31,560 --> 01:08:34,380
Knock, knock. Can I join you? 

966
01:08:34,390 --> 01:08:36,620
Sure.

967
01:08:41,700 --> 01:08:44,420
Guess the news of the 
 engagement came 
 as a bit of a shock, huh? 

968
01:08:44,440 --> 01:08:46,130
Basically.

969
01:08:46,140 --> 01:08:49,560
You know, I remember 
 what it was like to be 11.

970
01:08:49,570 --> 01:08:53,200
I had my first beau at 11. 
 It's a wonderful age.

971
01:08:53,210 --> 01:08:57,140
You're just starting to feel 
 like a woman and, 
 believe it or not, 

972
01:08:57,150 --> 01:09:00,610
soon you'll understand 
 what it's like to be in love.

