1421
01:37:26,360 --> 01:37:29,050
Well, then, here's to, uh...

1422
01:37:29,260 --> 01:37:32,080
Our daughters.

1423
01:37:32,100 --> 01:37:34,120
Our daughters.

1424
01:37:40,770 --> 01:37:42,530
Now I know how a goldfish feels.

1425
01:37:42,540 --> 01:37:45,530
<i>(groans) </i>

1426
01:37:45,540 --> 01:37:48,200
You know, sometime 
 if we're ever really alone, 

1427
01:37:48,210 --> 01:37:53,270
maybe we could talk about 
 what happened between us.

1428
01:37:54,020 --> 01:37:56,310
It all feels a bit hazy to me now.

1429
01:37:56,320 --> 01:37:59,540
It ended so fast.

1430
01:37:59,560 --> 01:38:02,110
It started so fast.

1431
01:38:02,130 --> 01:38:05,250
Well, that part 
 I remember perfectly.

1432
01:38:09,200 --> 01:38:11,320
Looks like things are heating up quite nicely.

1433
01:38:11,330 --> 01:38:13,830
I'd say it's safe to serve 
 the vichyssoise.

1434
01:38:13,840 --> 01:38:15,230
You ladle, I'll serve.

1435
01:38:19,330 --> 01:38:21,330
I'm sorry.


1355
01:38:26.564 --> 01:38:29.901
Yes, I'll...
uh, ladle.

1356
01:38:30.068 --> 01:38:33.696
Right.
And then I'll--

1357
01:38:33.863 --> 01:38:35.698
- Serve?
- Right.

1358
01:38:35.865 --> 01:38:37.700
Right.

1359
01:38:37.867 --> 01:38:43.581
So... you've done
fantastically well. Um...

1360
01:38:43.748 --> 01:38:47.752
your dream of owning your own
vineyard actually came true.

1361
01:38:47.919 --> 01:38:49.921
What about you?
You were always drawing...

1362
01:38:50.088 --> 01:38:52.757
on napkins
and corners of newspapers.

1363
01:38:52.924 --> 01:38:57.428
- Now you're this major designer.
- Yeah, it's great.

1364
01:38:57.595 --> 01:39:00.014
We both actually got
where we wanted to go.

1365
01:39:00.181 --> 01:39:02.558
Yeah, we did.

1366
01:39:04.852 --> 01:39:08.356
Anyway, what are we going
to do about the girls?

1367
01:39:08.523 --> 01:39:11.192
Well, now that they met,
we can't very well keep them apart.

1368
01:39:11.359 --> 01:39:14.612
Well, I could keep them for half of
the year, and then you could keep them.

1369
01:39:14.779 --> 01:39:17.448
- Well--
- Guys. They can't go to
two different schools every year.

1370
01:39:17.615 --> 01:39:19.617
- That's nuts.
- I agree.

1371
01:39:19.784 --> 01:39:21.702
Well, then, I could keep them both for
a whole year, and you could keep them...

1372
01:39:21.869 --> 01:39:23.704
Liz.

1373
01:39:23.871 --> 01:39:25.706
That's why we came up with--

1374
01:39:25.873 --> 01:39:30.795
Oh, G-- Sorry. Ignore me.
Enjoy your soup.

1375
01:39:30.962 --> 01:39:33.881
That's why we came up
with the solution that we have.

1376
01:39:34.048 --> 01:39:36.843
Really?
I thought it was because...

1377
01:39:37.009 --> 01:39:39.512
we decided never to see
each other again.

1378
01:39:39.679 --> 01:39:42.098
Not we, Liz.

1379
01:39:42.265 --> 01:39:45.810
Well, you know, that part's become
a bit hazy to me, too, over the years.

1380
01:39:45.977 --> 01:39:50.440
- You don't remember the day you packed?
- No, that day I remember perfectly.

1381
01:39:50.606 --> 01:39:52.775
Did I hurt you when
I threw that, um...

1382
01:39:52.942 --> 01:39:56.612
- What was it? Uh, uh--
- It was... a hair dryer.

1383
01:39:56.779 --> 01:39:57.999
Oh, right.

01:39:59.000 --> 01:40:01.659
 Sorry.

1384
01:40:03.786 --> 01:40:07.748
You know, I may never
be alone with you again.

1385
01:40:07.915 --> 01:40:12.837
So, about that day that you packed--
Why'd you do it?

1386
01:40:13.004 --> 01:40:15.256
Oh, Nick.
We were so young...

1387
01:40:15.423 --> 01:40:18.467
and we both had tempers.

1388
01:40:18.634 --> 01:40:21.470
We said stupid things
and so I packed.

1389
01:40:21.637 --> 01:40:23.681
Got on
my very first 747,

1390
01:40:23.848 --> 01:40:28.686
and... you didn't
come after me.

1391
01:40:28.853 --> 01:40:31.522
I didn't know that
you wanted me to.

1392
01:40:34.358 --> 01:40:36.444
Well, it doesn't
really matter any more.

1393
01:40:36.611 --> 01:40:39.363
So, let's just
put a good face on...

1394
01:40:39.530 --> 01:40:42.617
for the girls and get the show
on the road, huh?

1395
01:40:42.783 --> 01:40:46.245
Yeah, sure.
Let's...

1396
01:40:46.412 --> 01:40:48.998
get the show
on the road.

1397
01:40:55.046 --> 01:40:57.632
Your passport, Ms James.
Have a safe trip home.

1398
01:40:58.257 --> 01:40:59.634
Thank you.

1399
01:40:59.800 --> 01:41:03.471
- All set then. Where's Annie?
- I just rang up. She's on her way down.

1400
01:41:03.638 --> 01:41:05.473
Right.

1401
01:41:07.725 --> 01:41:09.894
So, I'll send Hallie
back to you over Christmas.

1402
01:41:10.061 --> 01:41:13.898
And Annie will spend Easter with you.

1403
01:41:18.653 --> 01:41:21.197
Honey, what are you doing in those
clothes? We've got a plane to catch.

1404
01:41:21.364 --> 01:41:26.077
Here's the deal, Mom.
We thought it over, and
we decided we're being totally gypped.

1405
01:41:26.243 --> 01:41:30.665
Dad promised we'd go on our camping
trip. And we want to go... together.

1406
01:41:30.831 --> 01:41:32.792
What camping trip?

1407
01:41:32.959 --> 01:41:35.211
The one we go on every summer
before school starts.

1408
01:41:35.378 --> 01:41:37.296
Annie, this is ridiculous.
Go upstairs and put your clothes on.

1409
01:41:37.463 --> 01:41:40.383
- Are you sure I'm Annie?
- Well, of course, I'm sure.

1410
01:41:40.549 --> 01:41:43.500
But, it's kind of hard
to be 100% positive, isn't it?

1411
01:41:43.501 --> 01:41:48.224
Girls, this is totally unfunny.
You're gonna make your mother
miss her aeroplane.

1412
01:41:48.391 --> 01:41:50.184
- Annie !
- Yes !

1413
01:41:58.234 --> 01:42:00.319
This one's Hallie.
I'm positive.

1414
01:42:00.486 --> 01:42:02.446
You know, I hope
you're right, Dad.

1415
01:42:02.613 --> 01:42:06.701
Because you wouldn't want to send the
wrong kid all the way back to England.

1416
01:42:06.867 --> 01:42:08.703
Would you?

1417
01:42:15.209 --> 01:42:18.629
Here's our proposition.

1418
01:42:18.796 --> 01:42:20.923
We go back to Dad's house,
pack our stuff,

1419
01:42:21.090 --> 01:42:23.843
and the four of us leave
on the camping trip.

1420
01:42:24.009 --> 01:42:26.679
- The four of us?
- And when you bring us back,

1421
01:42:26.846 --> 01:42:30.141
- we'll tell you who's Annie
and who's Hallie.
- Or you do as we say,

1422
01:42:30.307 --> 01:42:35.146
and I take one of you back with me
to London whether you like it or not.

1423
01:42:41.360 --> 01:42:44.363
And what am I supposed to do
for three days? Sit home and knit?

1424
01:42:44.530 --> 01:42:46.991
Honey, we have kind of
a sticky situation.

1425
01:42:47.158 --> 01:42:52.329
- Sticky situation? What do you mean,
"sticky situation"? What exactly--

1426
01:42:54.248 --> 01:42:56.459
Excuse me.
What is she doing here?

1427
01:42:56.625 --> 01:42:58.461
You see, that's part of the deal.
The four of us--

1428
01:42:58.627 --> 01:43:01.088
We... go together.

1429
01:43:01.255 --> 01:43:03.757
- What are you suddenly,
the Brady Bunch? This is ridic.... Hello.

1430
01:43:03.924 --> 01:43:05.801
Everything all right?

1431
01:43:05.968 --> 01:43:07.803
Well, no. Actually it isn't.

1432
01:43:07.970 --> 01:43:11.015
I didn't realize that
you were going on this little outing.

1433
01:43:11.182 --> 01:43:15.060
- And to tell you the truth, I'm not
so sure that I'm okay with it.
- I agree.

1434
01:43:15.227 --> 01:43:18.564
I think the ex-wife in
the next sleeping bag is a little weird.

1435
01:43:18.731 --> 01:43:23.068
- Thank you.
- I absolutely insist that you come with us. Really.

1436
01:43:23.235 --> 01:43:24.321
Liz--

1437
01:43:24.322 --> 01:43:27.323
No, honestly, Nick.
I've messed up your entire weekend.

1438
01:43:27.489 --> 01:43:31.202
It's the least I can do.
Really, please.

1439
01:43:42.171 --> 01:43:44.006
Dad, what's Meredith
doing here?

1440
01:43:44.173 --> 01:43:47.593
- Your mother invited her.
- What?

1441
01:43:47.760 --> 01:43:49.595
Be nice.

1442
01:44:02.024 --> 01:44:05.986
- Okay. All set? Have fun, everyone.
- What?

1443
01:44:06.153 --> 01:44:08.239
Liz, what are
you doing?

1444
01:44:08.405 --> 01:44:12.493
Well, I really think that
you and Meredith need some time
alone before the big day.

1445
01:44:12.660 --> 01:44:14.620
Mom, come on !
That's not the plan.

1446
01:44:14.787 --> 01:44:17.039
Ah, honestly, you'll have
much more fun without me.

1447
01:44:17.206 --> 01:44:20.501
Wait, wait. If you're not going,
I certainly don't have to go.

1448
01:44:20.668 --> 01:44:22.503
I mean, trust me,
I'm not a big nature girl.

1449
01:44:22.670 --> 01:44:24.588
But this is your chance
to really get to know the girls.

1450
01:44:24.755 --> 01:44:27.508
I mean after all,
starting next week, they're--

1451
01:44:27.675 --> 01:44:29.510
they're half yours.

1452
01:44:35.391 --> 01:44:37.393
Have fun all of you !

1453
01:44:41.981 --> 01:44:43.816
Bye-bye !

1454
01:44:43.983 --> 01:44:47.987
Oh, I would pay big money
to see that woman climb a mountain.

1455
01:44:56.161 --> 01:44:58.414
Whoa !

1456
01:44:58.580 --> 01:45:02.126
- Come on, you guys.
- Whoa ! Oh !

1457
01:45:15.931 --> 01:45:20.310
Oh, I'm gonna
kill my trainer.

1458
01:45:20.477 --> 01:45:24.440
He says I'm in such great shape. I can't
believe people actually do this for fun.

1459
01:45:26.150 --> 01:45:28.152
Hold on.
We're stopping.

1460
01:45:28.318 --> 01:45:31.655
Again? Dad, at this rate,
it'll take us...

1461
01:45:31.822 --> 01:45:33.657
three days just
to get to the lake.

1462
01:45:33.824 --> 01:45:37.995
Meredith isn't used to the altitude.
Just chill, okay?

1463
01:45:38.162 --> 01:45:42.458
Ooh.

1464
01:45:42.624 --> 01:45:45.461
Ah, I'm in serious pain.

1465
01:45:45.627 --> 01:45:49.715
Somebody hand me my Evian.
I can't move.

1466
01:45:49.882 --> 01:45:51.967
Sure.

1467
01:45:56.180 --> 01:45:58.015
Brilliant.

1468
01:46:02.895 --> 01:46:04.730
Here you go, Mer.

1469
01:46:13.030 --> 01:46:16.533
Honey, you okay?
What happened?

1470
01:46:16.700 --> 01:46:19.703
This little guy was
on her Evian bottle.

1471
01:46:19.870 --> 01:46:22.664
Oh, he won't hurt you, Meredith.

1472
01:46:22.831 --> 01:46:25.000
Oh, right, right, right. Right. I know.

1473
01:46:25.001 --> 01:46:28.587
You, uh, go ahead.

1474
01:46:28.754 --> 01:46:30.839
I'll be fine.

1475
01:46:31.006 --> 01:46:33.258
Get that thing away from me.

1476
01:46:33.509 --> 01:46:34.593
I hate things that crawl.

1477
01:46:34.760 --> 01:46:37.971
Aagh ! How can you touch that?
Just put it down.

1478
01:46:38.138 --> 01:46:40.974
Okay. Okay.
I'll put it down.

1479
01:46:42.726 --> 01:46:46.188
- Girls?
- What?
- What?

1480
01:46:46.355 --> 01:46:49.525
I'm going to take the lead. The two
of you help Meredith. All right?

1481
01:46:49.691 --> 01:46:52.361
Sure, you'll help me.

1482
01:46:52.486 --> 01:46:56.031
Right over a cliff,
you'll help me.

1483
01:46:56.198 --> 01:46:59.534
- Not a bad idea.
- Yeah. See any cliffs?

1484
01:46:59.701 --> 01:47:02.371
- Aah, my backpack.
- Need a hand, Mer?

1485
01:47:04.790 --> 01:47:10.295
Not from you, thank you.
Don't think I can't see
right past those angelic faces.

1486
01:47:10.462 --> 01:47:12.297
One more trick from you two,
and I promise...

1487
01:47:12.464 --> 01:47:16.927
I will make your lives miserable
from the day I say "I do."

1488
01:47:17.094 --> 01:47:20.555
Got it?

1489
01:47:20.722 --> 01:47:24.184
Got it, Cruella.

1490
01:47:24.351 --> 01:47:27.271
What did you call me?

1491
01:47:27.437 --> 01:47:31.066
Nothing, nothing.
Not a thing, Cruella.

1492
01:47:31.233 --> 01:47:35.737
Oh, by the way, Mer, I think there's
something on your head.

1493
01:47:49.501 --> 01:47:53.880
Are you all right?

1494
01:47:54.047 --> 01:47:59.177
- Aah !
- What... happened?

1495
01:47:59.344 --> 01:48:03.348
Ask... them.

1496
01:48:03.521 --> 01:48:13.734
What did we do, Dad?
We were right behind you.

1497
01:48:17.571 --> 01:48:20.365
Here we go, girls.
This will hold us for a while.

1498
01:48:25.537 --> 01:48:27.706
Sure you don't want some trout, Mom?

1499
01:48:27.873 --> 01:48:30.208
Is that okay, by the way,
if we start calling you mom?

1500
01:48:30.375 --> 01:48:33.670
I think your mother would prefer if you called me Meredith.

1501
01:48:33.837 --> 01:48:39.301
And no thank you. 
I do not eat... trout... for the thousandth time.

1502
01:48:39.468 --> 01:48:41.762
I will wait until breakfast.

1503
01:48:41.928 --> 01:48:43.889
- What are we having?
- Trout.

1504
01:48:44.055 --> 01:48:46.641
Come on. It's part of the experience.

1505
01:48:46.808 --> 01:48:50.187
Mmm. And what's the other part?
Being eaten to death by mosquitoes?

1506
01:48:50.353 --> 01:48:52.898
God, you'd think
they actually like this stuff.

1507
01:48:53.064 --> 01:48:56.193
Well, what's that you're using?
Let me see that.

1508
01:48:59.696 --> 01:49:03.867
Well, you're gonna attract every mosquito in the state with this stuff,
It's sugar and water.

1509
01:49:04.034 --> 01:49:06.286

Where'd you get it?

1510
01:49:08.371 --> 01:49:11.917
That's it. 
I am taking one large sleeping pill...

1511
01:49:12.083 --> 01:49:14.085
and going to bed.

1512
01:49:20.884 --> 01:49:24.054
Meredith,
what are you doing?

1513
01:49:24.221 --> 01:49:27.641
I don't want the mountain lions to--

1514
01:49:27.807 --> 01:49:31.895
There are no mountain lions
up here, are there?

1515
01:49:33.647 --> 01:49:35.482
No.

1516
01:49:51.373 --> 01:49:53.208
Good night.

1517
01:49:57.712 --> 01:50:00.882
Girls, I'm telling you.
Lay off.

1518
01:50:01.049 --> 01:50:04.094
This isn't her thing, okay?
I'm not marrying her because she's Annie Oakley.

1519
01:50:04.261 --> 01:50:06.096
Who's Annie Oakley?

1520
01:50:06.263 --> 01:50:09.349
Just cool it.

1521
01:50:25.699 --> 01:50:27.993
Come on. Come on.

1522
01:50:28.159 --> 01:50:29.995
Okay.

1523
01:50:30.161 --> 01:50:33.498
I hope that
one large sleeping pill worked.

1524
01:50:41.047 --> 01:50:43.633
You take that side.
- All right.

1525
01:50:46.803 --> 01:50:51.266
- Gosh, she's heavy.
- She's also like... snoring.

1526
01:50:59.524 --> 01:51:02.485
Nicky?

1527
01:51:29.179 --> 01:51:32.432
Sweet dreams, Mommie Dearest.

1528
01:51:47.739 --> 01:51:52.202
Mmm.
That feels nice.

1529
01:52:02.253 --> 01:52:05.590
Nicky !

1530
01:52:08.259 --> 01:52:11.471
Oh, man.

1531
01:52:11.638 --> 01:52:13.473
Ooh !

1532
01:52:20.104 --> 01:52:21.940
Ugh !

1533
01:52:24.776 --> 01:52:27.904
Ugh ! Ugh !

1534
01:52:28.071 --> 01:52:31.074
- What's goin' on?
- Here's what's going on, buddy !

1535
01:52:31.241 --> 01:52:34.786
The day we get married is the day
I ship those brats off to Switzerland.

1536
01:52:34.953 --> 01:52:39.874
Get the picture?
It's me or them. Take your pick.

1537
01:52:42.168 --> 01:52:44.379
- Them.

1538
01:52:44.546 --> 01:52:49.592
- Excuse me?
- T-H-E-M, them.

1539
01:52:49.759 --> 01:52:51.594
Get the picture?

1540
01:53:08.778 --> 01:53:11.531
Hello.
You're back so soon.

1541
01:53:11.698 --> 01:53:15.201
- Did you have fun?
- Well, I wouldn't go right to fun.

1542
01:53:15.368 --> 01:53:19.372
- You wouldn't?
- We've been punished to the end of the century.

1543
01:53:19.539 --> 01:53:24.252
- Starting now. Go !
- Where's Meredith?

1544
01:53:24.419 --> 01:53:30.000
We played a couple of harmless tricks on her and she kind of freaked out a little.

1545
01:53:30.001 --> 01:53:33.428
A little?
Hmm.

1546
01:53:33.595 --> 01:53:36.889
She threw this at my head.

1547
01:53:37.056 --> 01:53:39.726
At least it's smaller than a hair dryer.

1548
01:53:39.851 --> 01:53:42.562
Oh, Nick, it's all my fault.
If I hadn't suggested she go--

1549
01:53:42.729 --> 01:53:46.190
Or tricked!
Tricked would be more like it.

1550
01:53:46.357 --> 01:53:48.484
Like mother,
like daughters.

1551
01:53:48.651 --> 01:53:50.486
I-I really am sorry.

1552
01:53:50.653 --> 01:53:53.323
- We are too, Dad. Really.
- Yeah.

1553
01:53:53.448 --> 01:53:55.950
Up to your room...
now.

1554
01:54:02.123 --> 01:54:04.542
I gotta remember
to thank them one day.

1555
01:54:08.880 --> 01:54:12.300
So, where's Chessy?
I'm starving.

1556
01:54:12.467 --> 01:54:17.680
Well, she and Martin went off on a picnic around noon... yesterday.

1557
01:54:17.847 --> 01:54:20.933
Really ! Who would
have thought-- my nanny, your butler !

1558
01:54:23.561 --> 01:54:26.314
Well, what do you say,
I whip us up something to eat?

1559
01:54:26.481 --> 01:54:31.819
- You can cook now?
- Oh, yeah. I can, uh, make pasta and pasta and, uh--

1560
01:54:31.986 --> 01:54:36.741
- Mmm, pasta sounds good.
- Well, pasta it is.

1561
01:54:42.288 --> 01:54:44.373
Okay, I'll take two.

1562
01:54:44.540 --> 01:54:49.629
- Hey, Dad!
- Wow! You look so nice!

1563
01:54:49.796 --> 01:54:54.467
- Where are you going?
- Good night, ladies.

1564
01:55:02.475 --> 01:55:06.896
- Oh, wow !
- This is where I keep my private stash.

1565
01:55:07.063 --> 01:55:09.357
Did you know
I also collect wine?

1566
01:55:09.524 --> 01:55:13.277
- Really?
- I'm a man of limited interest.
Come here.

1567
01:55:15.446 --> 01:55:19.617
This...
is a 1921 Burgundy.

1568
01:55:19.784 --> 01:55:25.456
- They say the rain that year made this
the best Burgundy ever harvested.
- Oh.

1569
01:55:25.623 --> 01:55:27.959
Now, you will appreciate this.
Come here.

1570
